---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Vowel-Heavy Rack Solutions in Scrabble — Dump, Play, or Exchange?"
  description="Stuck with AEIOU and more vowels than consonants? Learn the best vowel-heavy words, dump strategies, and when to exchange to get your rack back on track."
  keywords="vowel heavy rack scrabble, too many vowels, vowel dump words scrabble, aeiou rack strategy, scrabble vowel words, vowel excess strategy, multiple vowel words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Vowel-Heavy Rack Solutions in Scrabble — Dump, Play, or Exchange?",
    "description": "Stuck with AEIOU and more vowels than consonants? Learn the best vowel-heavy words, dump strategies, and when to exchange to get your rack back on track.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/vowel-heavy-rack-solutions" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a vowel-heavy rack in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A vowel-heavy rack has 5 or more vowels out of your 7 tiles (e.g., AEIOUAO). The ideal balance is 3-4 vowels and 3-4 consonants. With 5+ vowels you have limited scoring power and fewer valid word options, since most English words need consonants for structure." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best vowel dump words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The best vowel dump words use 3-4 vowels in a single play: ADIEU (4 vowels, 6 pts), AUDIO (4 vowels, 6 pts), OUIJA (4 vowels, 12 pts), QUEUE (4 vowels, 14 pts), AQUAE (4 vowels, 14 pts), and AALII (4 vowels, 5 pts). Two-vowel dumps include EAU (3 pts), OOH (6 pts), and AUA (3 pts)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I exchange tiles when I have too many vowels?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Exchange when you have 5+ vowels AND no valid vowel-dump word scores more than 8-10 points. If you can play ADIEU for 6 points while dumping 4 vowels, that's usually better than exchanging (which costs your entire turn). Only exchange if the bag has 7+ tiles remaining and your rack is truly unplayable." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Strategy</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Vowel-Heavy Rack Solutions in Scrabble — Dump, Play, or Exchange?</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">You look down at your rack and see AEIOUAO. Five vowels, two consonants, and no obvious plays. This is one of the most frustrating positions in Scrabble — but it's also one of the most manageable once you know the right words to dump excess vowels and the decision framework for when to exchange instead.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">🌊 Vowel Flood</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">VOWEL FLOOD? WORDS EXIST.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">42 valid Scrabble words use 3+ vowels in 5 letters or fewer</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Even racks like AAEIIOU have plays. The key is knowing your dump words before you need them.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 1: Recognizing a Vowel-Heavy Rack -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Recognizing a Vowel-Heavy Rack</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">The standard Scrabble bag contains 42 vowels (including 2 blanks that often become vowels) out of 100 tiles. A balanced rack holds 3-4 vowels and 3-4 consonants. When you hit 5 or more vowels, your scoring potential drops sharply because most high-value plays require consonant structure.</p>

      <!-- Stat Strip: Ideal vs Problematic -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">3V + 4C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Ideal balance</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4V + 3C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Slightly vowel-heavy</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">5V + 2C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Problematic</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">6V + 1C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Emergency</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300">The real danger isn't a single vowel-heavy draw — it's consecutive turns stuck with too many vowels. Each turn you fail to rebalance, the problem compounds. Recognizing the threshold early (5+ vowels) and acting immediately is the difference between losing 20 points over two turns or losing 60 over four.</p>

      <!-- Insight Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why Vowel Floods Happen</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The bag has 42 vowels vs 56 consonants (+ 2 blanks). Early game draws are roughly 40% vowels, but once consonants get played onto the board, the <span class="text-white font-medium">remaining bag becomes increasingly vowel-concentrated</span>. Mid-to-late game is when vowel floods hit hardest.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: Multi-Vowel Dump Words -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Multi-Vowel Dump Words You Must Memorize</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">These are your lifeline words — valid Scrabble plays that burn 3-4 vowels in a single turn. Memorize them before you need them. When a vowel flood hits, you should be reaching for these instantly, not scanning the board hoping something exists.</p>

      <!-- Table: Vowel-Heavy Valid Words -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Vowels Used</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">QUEUE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (UEUE)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Needs Q — best dump if available</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">AQUAE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (A-UA-E)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Plural of aqua — needs Q</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">OUIJA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (OUIA)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Valid in SOWPODS — high dump value</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">ADIEU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (A-IE-U)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Most common 4-vowel dump</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">AUDIO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (AU-IO)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Easy to place — common letters</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">AALII</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (AA-II)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Hawaiian shrub — burns double A/I</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">URAEI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">4 (U-A-E-I)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Plural of uraeus — all different vowels</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">LOOIE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">3 (OO-IE)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Slang for lieutenant</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">OORIE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">4 (OO-IE)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Scottish — shivery, cold</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">AIOLI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">4 (A-IO-I)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Garlic mayo — very playable</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Card Grid: Dump Words by Vowel Count -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟢 2-Vowel Dumps (Quick Relief)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">EAU (3), OOH (6), AAH (6), AIA (3), OOT (3), OOF (6), AUA (3), EEL (3) — fast plays that shed 2 vowels when you're slightly over-vowelled.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟡 3-Vowel Dumps (Moderate Fix)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">AEON (4), IDEA (5), ALOE (4), OBOE (6), EASE (4), ARIA (4), UVEA (7), TOEA (4) — solid mid-range dumps that rebalance without sacrificing too many points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟣 4-Vowel Dumps (Emergency)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ADIEU (6), AUDIO (6), OUIJA (12), AALII (5), AQUAE (14), URAEI (5), AIOLI (5) — these are your nuclear options for severe vowel floods.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔴 Vowel-Pair Words (Doubles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">AAHED (9), OORIE (5), AALII (5), LOOIE (5), OOZE (13) — these specifically target double vowels (AA, OO, II, EE) on your rack.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: Dump vs Exchange Decision Framework -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dump vs Exchange — The Decision Framework</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Every vowel-heavy turn presents the same three-way choice: play a vowel-dump word, exchange tiles, or make the best available play with what you have. The right decision depends on three factors — your score differential, tiles remaining in the bag, and what's on the board.</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps: Decision Process -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Decision Process</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Count your vowels.</span> 4 vowels = slightly heavy but playable. 5+ = action required immediately.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Scan for dump words.</span> Can you play ADIEU, AUDIO, OUIJA, or any 3-4 vowel word for 6+ points?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Check the bag.</span> Are there 7+ tiles remaining? Exchange is only valid when enough tiles remain. Under 7 tiles = you must play.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Compare scores.</span> If your best dump word scores &lt;6 and the bag has 7+ tiles, exchange 4-5 vowels. If dump word scores 6+, play it — tempo matters.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Cards: When to Dump vs Exchange -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Play a Dump Word When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">You can score 6+ points while shedding 3-4 vowels. You're ahead on points and want to maintain tempo. The bag has fewer than 7 tiles. You have a hook spot for ADIEU or AUDIO.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Exchange Tiles When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">No dump word scores above 5 points. You have 6+ vowels (catastrophic). The bag has 15+ tiles remaining. You're behind and need a bingo-capable rack next turn.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip: Exchange Cost vs Benefit -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">0 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Exchange scores</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">~25 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Opponent gains</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">35+ pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Your next turn potential</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ADIEU scores anyway</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300">The math usually favours playing a dump word. ADIEU for 6 points while shedding 4 vowels gives you a net swing of roughly +30 over two turns (6 now + better rack next turn) compared to exchanging (0 now + unknown next). Only exchange when your rack is truly catastrophic (AAEIIOU) and no dump word exists on the board.</p>

      <!-- Inline Cross-Links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/rack-management-basics/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Rack Management Basics — the complete guide to balancing your tiles</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/rack-leave-explained/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Rack Leave Explained — why what you keep matters more than what you play</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: Strategic Placement Tips -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Placement for Vowel-Heavy Words</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Knowing the words is half the battle. Placing them efficiently — maximizing score while opening as few premium squares to your opponent as possible — is the other half. Vowel-heavy words have unique placement considerations because they're mostly low-value tiles.</p>

      <!-- Purple Strategy Tips -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook onto existing consonants:</span> Words like ADIEU and AUDIO start or end with letters that hook well. Place them perpendicular to consonant-heavy words already on the board for cross-word bonus points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target Double Letter squares with consonants:</span> In ADIEU, the D is your only consonant. Place it on a DL square to double its value (2→4). In OUIJA, land the J on a DL for a 16-point swing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Avoid opening Triple Word lines:</span> Vowel dumps are low-scoring by nature. Don't compound the damage by giving your opponent access to a TW square on their next turn. Play defensively when dumping.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use the parallel play strategy:</span> Place vowel words parallel to existing words, creating 2-3 cross-words simultaneously. Even 1-point vowels add up when you score 3 cross-words at once.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Save your consonant for the leave:</span> If you play ADIEU (using A, D, I, E, U), you keep 2 tiles. Make sure those 2 tiles include your remaining consonant — never leave yourself with 2 vowels after a dump.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Insight Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Placement Math</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">OUIJA on a Double Word Score = 24 points. That's a <span class="text-white font-medium">legitimate scoring play</span>, not just a dump. Always scan for premium square combinations before settling for a basic placement.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5: Practice & Memorization -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Practice Drills for Vowel Floods</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">The worst time to learn dump words is when you're staring at AAEIIOU during a tournament game. Build your vowel-dump vocabulary now so it's automatic when you need it.</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps: Practice Routine -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Weekly Drill Routine</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Flashcard the top 10.</span> Write QUEUE, AQUAE, OUIJA, ADIEU, AUDIO, AALII, URAEI, AIOLI, OORIE, LOOIE on cards. Quiz yourself on vowel count + points for each.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Random rack challenge.</span> Draw 7 tiles with 5+ vowels from a bag. Find the best dump word within 30 seconds. Repeat 10 times.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Board placement practice.</span> Set up a mid-game board and find where ADIEU, AUDIO, or OUIJA fit. Focus on cross-word scoring and premium square access.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Exchange vs dump decision reps.</span> Given a rack and board photo, decide in 10 seconds: dump word, exchange, or best-available play. Track your accuracy over a week.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

